    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<div class=\"flex flex-row h-full \
w-full\">\n  \n<img src=\"/attachments/Night-15d.png?q=1\" height=\"600\" \
width=\"500\" class=\"mt-auto mb-auto\"/>\n\n<div class=\"flex flex-col \
flex-grow mt-auto mb-auto\">\n\n<h2 style=\"color:#ffecc9\">Large Faraday \
Rotation in Magnon-Polaron Modes of Fe<sub>2</sub>Mo<sub>3</sub>O<sub>8</sub> \
Polar Altermagnet Candidate</h2>\n\n<div class=\"text-left \
mt-4\">\n\nUniversity of Augsburg\n\n\nKirill \
Vasin\n\n</div>\n\n<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n<div class=\"flex \
flex-row dark-content\">\n\n  <div style=\"margin-left:auto; \
margin-top:-25px\">\n\n<img width=\"200\" height=\"200\" \
src=\"/attachments/cropped-logo_small-1.png\"/>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div \
style=\"margin-left:auto;\">\n\n<img width=\"250\" height=\"250\" \
src=\"/attachments/unia_logo.svg\"/>\n\n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div \
style=\"margin-left:auto;\">\n\n<img width=\"250\" height=\"250\" \
src=\"/attachments/image-66f.png\"/>\n\n    \n  </div>\n  \n\n\n  \n</div>\n  \
\n</div>\n\n</div>", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "a1eb4946-244c-4785-90ae-26f62db3bce6", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Fade" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## What is Faraday\nSince the audience is quite \
diverse, let me clarify:\n\n- Faraday Effect is a rotation of linearly \
polarized light in a medium with broken time-inversion symmetry and it is \
measured away from the resonance.  \n\n- MCD is a resonance effect. When \
absorption differs for clockwise or counterclockwise polarized light.\n\nBoth \
of them are two sides of the same coin.\n\nTraditionally Faraday is \
associated with ferromagnetic materials, where light couples to an axial \
magnetization vector. And it is not common for antiferromagnets to have it \
since the induced magnetization is weak; however, there are \
exceptions:\n\nFor antiferromagnets, it is mostly much, much smaller than \
these values.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "1bed55e2-336d-4d51-9353-7405bdb775fb", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## What is Faraday\nShow tables as well:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "5db4645a-8073-4ac2-a62d-655d20a2c673", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>Faraday Effect and \
Magneto-Circular Dichroism</MakeTitle>\n\n<Columns>\n\n<div>\n\n## \
Faraday\n\n\n<img width=\"400\" class=\"text-left\" style=\"margin:0\" \
src=\"/attachments/Faraday-74e.png?q=1\"/>\n\n\n- away from the resonance\n- \
phase effect\n- broken $T^{-1}$\n  \n</div>\n\n<div>\n\n## MCD\n\n<img \
class=\"text-left\" style=\"margin:0\" \
src=\"/attachments/MCD-4c7.png?q=1\"/>\n\n- resonance property\n- absorption \
effect\n- broken $T^{-1}$\n  \n</div>\n\n</Columns>\n\n<div \
class=\"fragment\">\n\nConventional antiferromagnets (local records):\n\n- \
EuTiO<sub>3</sub>$\\\\sim 2500\\~{}^\\circ/\\text{cm}$ (GHz);\n- \
FePS<sub>3</sub>$\\\\sim 600\\~{}^\\circ/\\text{cm}$ (THz)\n  \n</div>", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "8656942c-1fb4-4960-b4a9-c91098e6ac6c", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Structure\nIt is a known layered polar \
hexagonal antiferromagnet. It has two optically and magnetically active Fe2+ \
ions, which also show the magnetoelectric effect: you can induce macroscopic \
polarization by magnetic field and vice versa.\n\nThe absence of PT element \
in the symmetry satisfies the condition for altermagnetism. As you can see by \
the inset plot, even with high fields the induced magnetization remains \
zero.", "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "b3db89a6-16d7-4345-b6ac-06e41ad998f3", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".wlx\nInteractiveCrystalStructure := Module[{\n  rotation = \
0.01, slideId = CreateUUID[], \n  animate = CreateUUID[],\n  crystal = \
NotebookRead[NotebookStore[\"spay-943\"]]\n}, With[{\n  Widget = \
Graphics3D[\n    {\n      Translate[\n        Rotate[crystal, (0.4 \
Sin[rotation])//Offload], \n        \
{-2.670070204823249`,1.6115948364312345`,5.4499976387159395`}\n      ],\n     \
 AnimationFrameListener[rotation//Offload, \"Event\"->animate],\n      \
HemisphereLight[White, LightBlue, 0.5],\n      SpotLight[White, \
{6.417`,5.9913`,12.4225`}],\n      SpotLight[White, \
{-6.417`,-5.9913`,12.4225`}]\n    },\n\n    ImageSize -> {500, 500},\n    \
ViewPoint -> {5., 4., 2.},\n    \"BackgroundAlpha\"->1,\n    \
Background->Black,\n    Lighting->None,\n    \
\"OrthographicCameraZoom\"->0.3,\n    \"CameraNearPlane\" -> -20,\n    \
\"CameraFarPlane\" -> 0\n  ]\n},\n\n EventHandler[slideId, {\n   \"Destroy\" \
| \"Left\" -> Function[Null,\n     EventRemove[animate];\n   ],\n\n   \
\"Slide\" -> Function[Null,\n     EventHandler[animate, Function[Null,\n      \
 rotation += 0.01;\n     ]]; \n     EventFire[animate, True];\n   ]\n }];\n\n \
<div>\n    <Widget/>\n    <SlideEventListener Id={slideId}/>\n </div>\n] ]", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "da362110-9a06-4a2c-a567-65e88cb91fdb", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True, "Fade" -> True|>, 
