    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Why bother?\nThe nature and optical properties \
of low-frequency excitations are quite puzzling. Raman study shows chiral \
phonons, Neutron scattering shows magnon-polarons: a hybrid of magnon and \
acoustic phonon away from the Gamma point.\n\nOf course it would be nice to \
catch the signature band splitting or hybridization at the Gamma point, where \
we can probe it with our basic optical tools. And see if we can use \
magnetic-point group analysis, which may not be applicable in the case of \
ideal altermagnets. This one is not ideal, of course.", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "2218a237-4897-4268-9a9e-e23f0821c33a", "Invisible" -> False, 
