   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Our tool\nLet's talk about how we probe it. \
Our tool is time-resolved spectroscopy.\nWe have a femtosecond laser that \
generates pulses. When they hit our antenna, the latter generates THz \
radiation that goes through our sample and then it is captured by a detector. \
Since it is time-resolved, we see both: phase and amplitude of the EM \
field.\n\nBy dividing the output by the input we get our transmission \
spectrum.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "0d95c9aa-3d91-4a2b-b341-ca54d588a902", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
