    "Hash" -> "5ccd545f-ea1f-4b5c-8f2d-c9a05781fec8", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True, "Fade" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Absorption data\nThat's what we see. It is \
published data, 3 modes:\n1. chiral phonon, so it will react to magnetic \
field\n2,3 magneto-polarons\n\nIt is important: the eigenstates of light are \
linearly polarized.\nWe need to apply magnetic field to see something \
interesting.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "eea300fc-764f-49c8-8278-cb25e8b3b5a5", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>THz Absorption \
Data</MakeTitle>\n\n<div class=\"flex flex-row justify-between \
w-full\">\n\n<THzPlotDefault>k</THzPlotDefault> <!-- .element: \
style=\"margin:0\" class=\"dark-content\" -->\n\n<div class=\"mt-10\">\n\n1. \
Chiral-phonon (<strong style=\"color:red\">el.-dip.</strong> active, Raman \
active)\n2. Magnon-polaron (<strong style=\"color:red\">el.-dip.</strong> and \
<strong style=\"color:green\">mag.-dip.</strong>, Raman active)\n3. \
Magnon-polaron (<strong style=\"color:red\">el.-dip.</strong> and <strong \
style=\"color:green\">mag.-dip.</strong>, Raman active)\n\n<div \
class=\"mt-4\">\n\n  All are visible below T<sub>N</sub>\n\n<br/><br/>\n\n  \
__Linearly polarized waves \[UpDownArrow] are the eigenstates of light inside \
the matter__\n\n</div>\n\n  \n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n<br/><br/>\n\n<span \
class=\"fragment\">What if we apply static magnetic field along EM wave \
propagation?</span>\n\n<Footer/>", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "e0b5de63-bf7e-491e-8c68-67a8d33661df", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Magnetic-point group\nMagnetic point group \
gives at a 6-fold screw axis (rotation combined with translation and time \
inversion). \n\nThe simplest case if we induce an external magnetic field B \
|| z, it reduces the symmetry to 3m. \n\nThis gives us the following shapes \
of the dielectric tensor, magnetic and magneto-electric responses. For B || z \
we get non-diagonal tensor elements - antisymmetric with respect to time \
reversal.\n\nTo fill them up, we need a response function. For that we use \
linear response - or the Kubo formula.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "4867f926-24df-41d9-81ff-3eb325bee2ed", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>Neumann and Curie \
Principle</MakeTitle>\n\n- AFM state \[LongRightArrow] \
6<sup>'</sup><sub>3</sub>m<sup>'</sup>m\n- <span class=\"fragment\">AFM state \
and B||z \[LongRightArrow] 3m<sup>'</sup></span>\n\n  \n<div class=\"fragment \
mt-2\">Material equations:</div>\n\n<div \
class=\"fragment\">\n$$\n\\\\mathbf{P} = \
\\\\epsilon_0\\\\Big(\\\\hat{\\\\varepsilon} \\\\mathbf{E} + \
\\\\hat{\\\\chi}^{(me)} \\\\mathbf{H}\\\\Big) \\\\\\\\\n\\\\mathbf{M} = \
\\\\frac{1}{\\\\mu_0}\\\\Big(\\\\hat{\\\\mu} \\\\mathbf{H} - \
\\\\hat{\\\\chi}^{(me)} \\\\mathbf{E} \
\\\\Big)\n$$\n</div>\n\n\n$$\n\t\\hat{\\varepsilon}=\\left( \
\\begin{array}{ccc}\t\n\t\\varepsilon_{xx}^{(S)} & \\varepsilon_{xy}^{(A)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t-\\varepsilon_{xy}^{(A)} & \\varepsilon_{xx}^{(S)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t0 & 0 & \\varepsilon_{zz}^{(S)}\\\\\\\\\n\t\\end{array}\\right), \
\\\\quad \\hat{\\mu}=\\left( \\begin{array}{ccc}\t\n\t\\mu_{xx}^{(S)} & \
\\mu_{xy}^{(A)} & 0\\\\\\\\\n\t-\\mu_{xy}^{(A)} & \\mu_{xx}^{(S)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t0 & 0 & \\mu_{zz}^{(S)}\\\\\\\\\n\t\\end{array}\\right), \
\\\\\\\\\n\\text{}\n \\\\\\\\\n \\hat{\\chi}^{(me)}=\\left( \
\\begin{array}{ccc}\t\n\t\\chi_{xx}^{(S)} & \\chi_{xy}^{(A)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t-\\chi_{xy}^{(A)} & \\chi_{xx}^{(S)} & 0\\\\\\\\\n\t0 & 0 & \
\\chi_{zz}^{(S)}\\\\\\\\\n\t\\end{array}\\right)\n$$ <!-- .element: \
class=\"fragment\" -->\n\n<Footer/>", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "5ff68f66-d4d8-4b98-8071-81a332ca4043", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Fade" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "FigModel = NotebookRead[NotebookStore[\"opus-a5f\"]];", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "15204289-1d68-4a8b-97f4-d5dc1a2ab4d5", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Linear response\nWe can say, ok. Every mode in \
ground state is doubly degenerate, when we apply the field we should see \
Zeeman's effect, that resolves it into two branches. Then it must be just two \
modes, which share the same parameters. Expect the eigen energy is offset by \
some number - delta.\n\nAnd for each of the oscillators we can estimate the \
magnitude using two matrix elements: electric p and magnetic m dipole \
transition amplitudes.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "ee1050df-6050-4de5-b16b-8e24501a836d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>Zeeman \
Effect</MakeTitle>\n\n<Columns>\n\n<FigModel/>\n\n<div>\n\n- 2 oscillators \
per mode\n- 3 contributions:\n  - electric $p^2 \\\\rightarrow \
\\\\varepsilon$\n  - magnetic $m^2 \\\\rightarrow \\\\mu$\n  - \
magneto-electric $p m \\\\rightarrow \\\\chi$\n\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n\n- use \
Kubo formula to get $\\\\varepsilon$, $\\\\mu$ and \
$\\\\chi$\n</div>\n\n</Columns>\n\n<Footer/>", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "db019bdc-31cc-46d7-8cf8-7181902b2bb4", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Solution of Maxwell's equations\nThen \
Maxwell's equations gives 4 possible waves with 4 refractive indexes:\n\n- \
CW, CCW, and +/- k - propagation direction\n\nIt might look horribly for you, \
but you can find that this only depends on 4 real-valued numbers. Basically \
we reduced 27 complex tensor components to 4 numbers, that you can measure in \
zero field and then you know everything about your system.", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "4dd4bc02-df73-4952-8d63-d06df0cacc79", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>Solution of Maxwell's \
Equations</MakeTitle>\nFor the light propagating along the field direction \
$k|| B ||z$:\n\n$$\n\\\\begin{align*}\nn_{\\circlearrowleft}^{\\pm \
k}&=\\sqrt{\\left(1+\\frac{4 m^2 \\omega _0}{\\omega _0^2-(\\delta +i \\eta \
+\\omega )^2}\\right) \\left(\\varepsilon _0^{(xx)}+\\frac{4 p^2 \\omega \
_0}{\\omega _0^2-(\\delta +i \\eta +\\omega )^2}\\right)}\\pm\\frac{4 \\delta \
 m p}{-\\omega _0^2+(\\delta +i \\eta +\\omega )^2} \
\\\\\\\\\nn\\_{\\circlearrowright}^{\\pm k}&=\\sqrt{\\left(1+\\frac{4 m^2 \
\\omega _0}{\\omega _0^2-(-\\delta +i \\eta +\\omega )^2}\\right) \
\\left(\\varepsilon _0^{(xx)}+\\frac{4 p^2 \\omega _0}{\\omega _0^2-(-\\delta \
+i \\eta +\\omega )^2}\\right)}\\mp\\frac{4 \\delta  m p}{-\\omega \
_0^2+(-\\delta +i \\eta +\\omega )^2}\n\\\\end{align*}\n$$\n\nHere: \n\n- \
$\\delta = g~|B_z|$;\n- $m,p$ are real-valued numbers - measured at __0 \
field__;\n- 4 real-valued parameters define all optical properties!\n\n- for \
any transmitted light: <!-- .element: class=\"fragment\" \
-->\n\n$$\n\\\\begin{align*}\nS_{\\circlearrowright/\\circlearrowleft}^{(\\\\\
pm k)}(\\omega) \\propto exp\\Big(-\\frac{i \
n_{\\circlearrowright/\\circlearrowleft}^{(\\\\pm k)} \\omega \
L}{c}\\Big)\n\\\\end{align*}\n$$ <!-- .element: class=\"fragment\" -->\n\n- \
eigenstates of light are circular \:27f3\:27f3 <!-- .element: \
class=\"fragment\" -->\n", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "37b27870-882f-44ae-b465-06f2c96fc857", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## How to measure\nExplain", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "5a8fe4dc-70af-45e6-8c17-8a2e0e733529", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## How to measure\nExplain", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "8d0f8988-4d6c-4de8-9f8a-25c0d729d5cb", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## How to measure circular polarized light?\nIt \
is not obvious how to do that. We need two measurements with the analyzer set \
to +/- 45 degrees from the polarizer, then we recombine the signal to get \
circular polarized basis. And then take the ratio.\n\nTo disentangle Faraday \
effect or MCD from other non-reciprocal effects, we enforce it has to be odd \
in B and even in k.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "a0b373a4-1375-43fa-b8ce-66d16504b3fe", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nActual slide:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "64045d5b-e7c7-49ba-b109-dc9ba97a7a93", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Actual slide:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "ab22dde8-907e-4072-8049-dea40c80a6d4", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>How to measure \:27f3 \
polarized light?</MakeTitle>\n\n<Columns>\n\n<img class=\"dark-content\" \
src=\"/attachments/Screenshot-2026-03-10-at-16.49.00-64a.png\" \
width=\"400\"/>\n\n<div>\n\n\n- \
$S_{\\circlearrowright/\\circlearrowleft}(\\omega) = S_{+45} \\\\pm \
i(S_{-45})$\n- Take the ratio: $S = \
S_{\\circlearrowright}/S_{\\circlearrowleft}$\n\n<br/><br/>\n\nSignal \
extraction (odd in B, even in k): <!-- .element: class=\"fragment\" \
-->\n\n$$\nS_{MCD/F} = \\left\\\\{\\frac{S^{(+k,+B)} \\cdot \
S^{(-k,+B)}}{S^{(+k,-B)} \\cdot S^{(-k,-B)}} \\right\\\\}^{1/4}\n$$ <!-- \
.element: class=\"fragment\" -->\n  \n</div>\n\n</Columns>\n", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "e70e6f9c-5a0d-4f19-9d54-155e9ac5becc", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## Results\nShow all important results", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "8256c353-2e43-40eb-bb25-036545c63b80", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## Results\nShow all important results", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "4f9535af-fa30-43e0-bdbe-b984fdf252e6", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Results\nIf we just take the modulus of it, we \
see a nice V-shape splitting.\nEach branch is 100% polarized and the \
g-factors nicely agree with the Raman study.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "ac9ebfb4-d929-40b3-acad-e823bd9bc0b0", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nCompute or import finished figure:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "3ea56348-e4a2-4cad-911c-b53351bb7150", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Compute or import finished figure:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "f90bf136-78a6-45fe-b276-0581d413ab6f", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> 
     "MCDFigure = NotebookRead[NotebookStore[\"deflationary-730\"]];", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "9c656d4a-dc07-478c-a53f-be1bba0b5603", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nActual slide", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "19d8f998-6114-44c7-9d64-ba952ce9d074", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Actual slide", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "24792701-9f09-4502-9981-e785b91094b6", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle><strong>Our Data</strong>: \
Magneto-Circular Dichroism</MakeTitle>\n\n<Columns>\n\n<div>\n  \
\n<MCDFigure/> \n  \n</div>\n\n<div \
style=\"margin-top:5rem\">\n\n$$\nMCD(\\omega) = \
-log(|S_{MCD/F}(\\omega)|^2)\n$$\n\n<br/><br/>\n\n- characteristic V-shape \
splitting of antiferromagnet\n- each branch is 100% polarized\n- g-factor is \
confirmed by Raman study <small>Nature Physics volume 19, 1868\[Dash]1875 \
(2023)</small>\n  \n</div>\n\n</Columns>\n", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "9c07175b-71ee-4a28-976b-df8a30f8325d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nInteractive figure-widget, which reacts on the second \
fragment and shows calculated lines:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "046ca5f5-57b8-44f4-980c-1b7e4fb29544", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Interactive figure-widget, which reacts on the second \
fragment and shows calculated lines:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "1c0c6c25-7700-48d8-ba2d-cbab203dd84d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".wlx\nFigFaraday = \
NotebookRead[NotebookStore[\"prankster-177\"]];\n\nfaradayLines = {{}, \
{}};\nfaradayLinesFinale = \
NotebookRead[NotebookStore[\"leucotomy-367\"]];\nFigFaradayWidget := \
With[{event = EventObject[]}, \nEventHandler[event, {\n  \"Destroy\" | \
\"Left\" -> Function[Null,\n    faradayLines = {{}, {}};\n  ],\n  \
\"fragment-2\" -> Function[Null,\n    faradayLines = faradayLinesFinale;\n  \
]\n}];\n\n<div>  \n  <FigFaraday/> \n  <SlideEventListener \
Id={event}/>\n</div>\n]", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "44f7cd38-2c1d-4c7b-9207-4f8247cc7327", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n### Faraday\nNow if we look at phase - take the \
argument of it, we get Faraday rotation angle. Here it is at fixed magnetic \
field.\n\nAnd look, if we stay between two modes, we can still have linear \
polarized light but the rotation angle is 6000 degrees per cm. This is large, \
much larger than a conventional antiferromagnet.\n\nNow if we use our model \
derived from magnetic-point group analysis:\n\nyou see it perfectly lines up \
with experimental data. Even though we used zero-field data for oscillator \
parameters. \n\nFor the physics: but it gives large angle: magnetic and \
electric dipole transitions boosted by polarizability of the crystal - \
epsilon_infty.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "7f2701d5-e231-4d57-aa5b-86efd8071a66", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Faraday and other effects:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "4e5c05a8-3676-4018-b32b-926e5f9481d6", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle><strong>Our Data</strong>: \
Faraday Effect</MakeTitle>\n\n<Columns>\n\n<div class=\"dark-content\">\n  \
<FigFaradayWidget/>\n</div>\n\n<div \
style=\"margin-top:5rem\">\n\n$$\n\\theta_F(\\omega) = \\frac{\\omega \
L}{c}arg(S_{MCD/F}(\\omega))\n$$\n\n<br/><br/>\n\n- large Faraday rotation: \
$\\color{red}6000~{}^\\circ/\\text{cm}$\n- for conventional antiferromagnets \
like EuTiO<sub>3</sub>$\\\\sim 2500\\~{}^\\circ/\\text{cm}$ (GHz), \
FePS<sub>3</sub>$\\\\sim 600\\~{}^\\circ/\\text{cm}$ (THz)\n  \
\n</div>\n\n</Columns>\n\nFrom our model: <!-- .element: class=\"fragment\" \
-->\n\n$$\n\\theta_{F} = \\\\Re ~ \\frac{\\omega L}{2c} \
\\Bigg(\\sqrt{\\left(1+\\frac{4 m^2 \\omega _0}{\\omega _0^2-(\\delta +i \
\\eta -\\omega )^2}\\right) \\left(\\varepsilon\\_\\infty^{(xx)}+\\frac{4 p^2 \
\\omega _0}{\\omega _0^2-(\\delta +i \\eta -\\omega )^2}\\right)} \n$$ <!-- \
.element: class=\"fragment\" -->\n\nFrom zero-field data: <!-- .element: \
class=\"fragment\" -->\n\n$$ \np = 0.31, ~m = 0.22, \
~\\varepsilon_\\infty^{(xx)} = 22.4\n$$<!-- .element: class=\"fragment\" \
-->\n\n- polar structure gives a boost to magnetic-dipole transitions <!-- \
.element: class=\"fragment\" -->\n\n", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "ba8b1aed-1ae9-417b-8e19-82e4c07d7d3b", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## Summary\nThe end of the presentation:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "050fb7a0-9454-449d-b159-709d4d488e3a", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## Summary\nThe end of the presentation:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "e2f877e8-362d-4497-869c-a7cbd50a0043", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "speaker.md\n## Summary\nThere are still open questions:\n\n- \
role of hybridization\n- in principle the framework we used does only need \
matrix elements p and m, we can assume that the phonon wavefunction is there \
as well and it gives a nice boost to the effect.\n- how to use or should we \
use spin-group analysis for that;\n- the same effect found in CMO, which is \
again an altermagnet candidate and also shows large Faraday rotation.", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "07fb93bb-bd53-487c-86d3-b86a8a523369", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> False|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nActual slide:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "31986cae-4867-4eba-8a58-3bc879334498", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Actual slide:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "775e76d5-b7fc-4449-800a-4686bb8958a5", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "9d01a796-6ef9-4d6d-bafa-4fb630c0bb77"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".slide\n<!-- .slide: class=\"slide-standard slide-dark\" \
data-background-color=\"black\" -->\n\n<MakeTitle>Summary</MakeTitle>\n\n<div \
style=\"\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, \
minmax(400px, 2fr));\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    gap:30px;\n    \
align-content: space-between;\n    align-items: start;\n    justify-items: \
stretch;\n\">\n\n\n<div class=\"fragment\">\n  \n- Curie and Neumann \
principle works at $\\Gamma$ point for non-perfect altermagnets in a case of \
Faraday/MCD effects\n\n$$\n\\hat{\\varepsilon}=\\left( \
\\begin{array}{ccc}\t\n\t\\varepsilon_{xx}^{(S)} & \\varepsilon_{xy}^{(A)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t-\\varepsilon_{xy}^{(A)} & \\varepsilon_{xx}^{(S)} & \
0\\\\\\\\\n\t0 & 0 & \
\\varepsilon_{zz}^{(S)}\\\\\\\\\n\t\\end{array}\\right)\n$$\n\n\n</div>\n<div \
class=\"fragment\">\n  \n- Large Faraday rotation was found in \
magneto-electric modes in Fe<sub>2</sub>Mo<sub>3</sub>O<sub>8</sub> \
altermagnet candidate\n\n<div class=\"dark-content\">\n  \
\n<FigFaraday/>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"fragment\">\n  \n- We \
provide a general approach on how to build/characterize full optical response \
